               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipits and headings of the texts; a few lines, alternating with black lines, on the inicipit of Texts I-1), I-2); numbers of the miracles (not always); elements of the punctuation signs; caesura markers.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The inner corners of fols.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES153176">153-176</ref>are damaged and have been repaired by means of pieces of parchment made out from a different Ms. (containing an unidentified more recent text, s. fols. 170v, 171v, 172v, 173r, 174r, 175r), sewn to the fol. by means of parchment strips (fols.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES153163">153-163</ref>,<ref type="mss" corresp="ES166169">166-169</ref>, 176), and by means of threads (fols.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES164165">164-165</ref>,<ref type="mss" corresp="ES170175">170-175</ref>).</note>
                     <note>- The introductory exhortation (Text I-4) is repeted twice.</note>
                     <note>- Text I-4 (fols. 69rb-70vb), numbered as miracle n. 56 and placed right before the miracle, is arranged in different strophes (divided by means of nine dots asterisk and six dots colons in fols. 69v-70v).</note>
                     <note>- Compressed script on fols. 88vb, 161vb.</note>
                  </msItem>
